Most likely you have these ingredients in the house, but if you don’t a quick trip to the grocery store will set you up. Pick up creamy peanut butter, powdered sugar and honey for the play dough. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f9/Make-Edible-Play-Dough-and-Finger-Paint-Step-1Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Make-Edible-Play-Dough-and-Finger-Paint-Step-1Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/f9/Make-Edible-Play-Dough-and-Finger-Paint-Step-1Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Make-Edible-Play-Dough-and-Finger-Paint-Step-1Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":307,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":507.3626373626374,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Purchase white sugar, corn starch and food coloring to create the finger paint. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/3c/Make-Edible-Play-Dough-and-Finger-Paint-Step-1Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Make-Edible-Play-Dough-and-Finger-Paint-Step-1Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/3/3c/Make-Edible-Play-Dough-and-Finger-Paint-Step-1Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Make-Edible-Play-Dough-and-Finger-Paint-Step-1Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":307,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":507.3626373626374,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Combine the sugar, corn starch and water in a pan and simmer over low heat. Whisk frequently until mixture thickens to a pudding-like consistency. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/17/Make-Edible-Play-Dough-and-Finger-Paint-Step-5Bullet1.jpg/v4-460px-Make-Edible-Play-Dough-and-Finger-Paint-Step-5Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/17/Make-Edible-Play-Dough-and-Finger-Paint-Step-5Bullet1.jpg/v4-760px-Make-Edible-Play-Dough-and-Finger-Paint-Step-5Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":307,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":507.3626373626374,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Remove from heat and allow it time to cool. Once it has cooled you can either separate into bowls and add color or make one batch of a single color. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/43/Make-Edible-Play-Dough-and-Finger-Paint-Step-5Bullet2.jpg/v4-460px-Make-Edible-Play-Dough-and-Finger-Paint-Step-5Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/4/43/Make-Edible-Play-Dough-and-Finger-Paint-Step-5Bullet2.jpg/v4-760px-Make-Edible-Play-Dough-and-Finger-Paint-Step-5Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":307,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":507.3626373626374,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
